cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with language models and sentiment analysis. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves training models to learn representations. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves unsupervised learning and discovering high-level concepts. The use of recurrent models and generative processes could also place it under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper's focus on sentiment analysis and the use of natural language could also make it relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as sentiment analysis is often used in image and video analysis.
